      "content": "I understand the concern about religious freedom, but allowing religious groups to opt out of certain government laws, especially those related to taxes and healthcare, would create a dangerous precedent. It would essentially mean that religious beliefs could override the laws that apply to everyone, leading to inequality and potential discrimination. A secular state is meant to ensure that all citizens, regardless of their religious beliefs, are subject to the same laws and protections. This doesn't mean religious freedom doesn't exist; rather, it means that religious freedom must be balanced with the rights and freedoms of all citizens. Allowing religious exemptions in these areas could undermine the very foundation of a fair and just society.",
      "source": "target",
